Note:
==============================================================================
ECDSA - FIPS 186-4 Elliptic Curve Digital Signature Algorithm
==============================================================================

Implements ECDSA over NIST curves P-256, P-384, P-521 with:

1. Deterministic nonce generation per RFC 6979 section 3.2.
   The per-message k value is derived from the private key and message
   hash via a HMAC-DRBG construction. This eliminates the entire
   catastrophic class of failures from random-k bugs (Sony PS3 ECDSA
   attack in 2010; Bitcoin Android wallet k-reuse in 2013).

2. Hash selection per RFC 6979 section 4:
       P-256 -> SHA-256
       P-384 -> SHA-384
       P-521 -> SHA-512
   The hash output is reduced via bits2int with truncation to the order
   bit length before being used as the message digest in the signing
   equation.

3. Signature encoding: bare (r, s) returned as two BigInt buffers plus
   a DER serializer to RFC 5480 / SEC 1 v2.0 C.5 SEQUENCE { INTEGER r,
   INTEGER s } format. The DER parser is the inverse and is used by
   X.509 certificate signature verification (x509.runa).

4. Constant-time secret path:
   - Private scalar generation rejects with replacement when the
     candidate is >= n (a value-dependent loop, but the iteration count
     is biased so heavily toward acceptance that the leakage is
     dominated by the entropy source's own timing properties).
   - Scalar multiplication uses the curve module's constant-time
     Montgomery ladder (see curve_pXXX.runa).
   - k inversion uses bigint_mod_exp via Fermat (constant-time over
     loop bounds).
   - Final r-comparison in verify is bytewise compared in a public-time
     manner since r is public; we still use a constant-time helper.

5. Domain: signatures are NOT length-prefixed by the curve identifier;
   the calling protocol (X.509, TLS, SSH) is responsible for tagging.
   The DER serializer emits the canonical (r, s) tuple only.

References:
- NIST FIPS 186-4 (Digital Signature Standard).
- RFC 6979 "Deterministic Usage of the Digital Signature Algorithm".
- SEC 1: Elliptic Curve Cryptography v2.0 section 4.1.
- RFC 5480 (algorithm OIDs and signature encoding).
- Hankerson, Menezes, Vanstone "Guide to Elliptic Curve Cryptography"
  chapter 4 (ECDSA).
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/bigint.runa" as BigInt
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/bigint_extra.runa" as BigIntX
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/hmac.runa" as Hmac
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/sha2.runa" as Sha2
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/entropy.runa" as Entropy
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/secure_memory.runa" as SecureMem
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/curve_p256.runa" as P256
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/curve_p384.runa" as P384
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/curve_p521.runa" as P521
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/field_p256.runa" as F256
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/field_p384.runa" as F384
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/field_p521.runa" as F521

Note: Hash algorithm identifiers used internally to parametrize RFC 6979.
Constant ECDSA_HASH_SHA256 as Integer is 0
Constant ECDSA_HASH_SHA384 as Integer is 1
Constant ECDSA_HASH_SHA512 as Integer is 2

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Generic hash dispatch
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "ecdsa_hash_output_size" takes hash_id as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns the digest size in bytes for the named hash function.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    SHA-256 -> 32, SHA-384 -> 48, SHA-512 -> 64.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Single comparison.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Public dispatch.
    @End Security_Scope

    If hash_id is equal to ECDSA_HASH_SHA256:
        Return 32
    End If
    If hash_id is equal to ECDSA_HASH_SHA384:
        Return 48
    End If
    If hash_id is equal to ECDSA_HASH_SHA512:
        Return 64
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "ecdsa_hash_message" takes arena as Integer, hash_id as Integer, message as Integer, message_length as Integer, out_digest as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Dispatches to the appropriate SHA-2 variant for the curve.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Selects sha256_hash, sha384_hash, or sha512_hash.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Pure dispatch; cost is that of the underlying hash.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Public dispatch.
    @End Security_Scope

    If hash_id is equal to ECDSA_HASH_SHA256:
        Return proc sha256_hash from Sha2 with arena, message, message_length, out_digest
    End If
    If hash_id is equal to ECDSA_HASH_SHA384:
        Return proc sha384_hash from Sha2 with arena, message, message_length, out_digest
    End If
    If hash_id is equal to ECDSA_HASH_SHA512:
        Return proc sha512_hash from Sha2 with arena, message, message_length, out_digest
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "ecdsa_hmac_hash" takes arena as Integer, hash_id as Integer, key as Integer, key_length as Integer, message as Integer, message_length as Integer, out_tag as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Dispatches to HMAC over the SHA-2 variant identified by hash_id.
    Used by RFC 6979 deterministic-k generation.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Selects hmac_sha256, hmac_sha384, or hmac_sha512.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Pure dispatch.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time over message length per the chosen HMAC variant.
    @End Security_Scope

    If hash_id is equal to ECDSA_HASH_SHA256:
        Return proc hmac_sha256 from Hmac with arena, key, key_length, message, message_length, out_tag
    End If
    If hash_id is equal to ECDSA_HASH_SHA384:
        Return proc hmac_sha384 from Hmac with arena, key, key_length, message, message_length, out_tag
    End If
    If hash_id is equal to ECDSA_HASH_SHA512:
        Return proc hmac_sha512 from Hmac with arena, key, key_length, message, message_length, out_tag
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: BigInt bit-length helper
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "ecdsa_bit_length" takes bn as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns the bit length of a BigInt (1 + index of highest set bit).
    Used by RFC 6979 to compute the bit-truncation length qlen.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Walk limbs from high to low; find first non-zero; count its high
    bit position; combine with the limb index.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(limb_count) for the limb scan plus O(64) for the bit scan.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    The result depends on the input value; callers must invoke this
    only on public parameters such as the curve order n.
    @End Security_Scope

    If bn is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc bigint_get_limb_count from BigInt with bn
    Let li_plus_one be count
    While li_plus_one is greater than 0:
        Let li be li_plus_one minus 1
        Let lv be proc bigint_get_limb from BigInt with bn, li
        If lv is not equal to 0:
            Note: Limbs are u64 stored as signed int64. If bit 63 is set
            Note: (limb < 0 as signed), the bit length is 64. Otherwise we
            Note: count via `divided by 2` (which is safe for non-negative
            Note: values; equivalent to logical shift right by 1).
            If lv is less than 0:
                Return li multiplied by 64 plus 64
            End If
            Let bit_pos be 0
            Let lv_copy be lv
            While lv_copy is not equal to 0:
                Set lv_copy to lv_copy divided by 2
                Set bit_pos to bit_pos plus 1
            End While
            Return li multiplied by 64 plus bit_pos
        End If
        Set li_plus_one to li_plus_one minus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: RFC 6979 helpers: int2octets and bits2int / bits2octets
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "ecdsa_int_to_octets" takes bn as Integer, rolen as Integer, out_buffer as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Encodes a BigInt as a rolen-byte big-endian octet string per
    RFC 6979 section 2.3.3. rolen = ceil(qlen / 8).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Delegates to bigint_to_bytes_be with output capacity rolen.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(rolen) byte writes.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Constant time over rolen (no value-dependent branching).
    @End Security_Scope

    Return proc bigint_to_bytes_be from BigInt with bn, out_buffer, rolen
End Process

Process called "ecdsa_bits_to_int" takes arena as Integer, in_bytes as Integer, in_length as Integer, qlen as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Converts an octet string to a BigInt per RFC 6979 section 2.3.2.
    If the bit length of the input exceeds qlen, the high bits are
    discarded (right-shift by (8*in_length - qlen)).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Build a BigInt from the bytes (big-endian).
    2. If 8*in_length > qlen, shift right by the excess bit count.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    One BigInt construction plus O(excess_bits) shift loop.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    The shift count depends only on the public parameters qlen and
    in_length, not on the value being shifted. Constant-time over
    those parameters.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let bn be proc bigint_from_bytes_be from BigInt with arena, in_bytes, in_length
    If bn is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let in_bits be in_length multiplied by 8
    If in_bits is greater than qlen:
        Let excess be in_bits minus qlen
        Let shift_iter be 0
        While shift_iter is less than excess:
            proc bigint_shift_right_one from BigIntX with bn
            Set shift_iter to shift_iter plus 1
        End While
    End If
    Return bn
End Process

Process called "ecdsa_bits_to_octets" takes arena as Integer, in_bytes as Integer, in_length as Integer, qlen as Integer, rolen as Integer, n as Integer, out_buffer as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Implements bits2octets(in) = int2octets(bits2int(in) mod q) per
    RFC 6979 2.3.4.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. z1 = bits2int(in, qlen).
    2. z2 = z1 mod n.
    3. int2octets(z2, rolen, out_buffer).
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Dominated by the modular reduction.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Public-data only (the input is the message hash). The modular
    reduction uses bigint_mod which is not strictly constant-time over
    its inputs but the inputs here are public.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let z1 be proc ecdsa_bits_to_int with arena, in_bytes, in_length, qlen
    If z1 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let z2 be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
    If z2 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cmp be proc bigint_compare from BigInt with z1, n
    If cmp is less than 0:
        proc ecdsa_int_to_octets with z1, rolen, out_buffer
        Return 1
    End If
    proc bigint_mod from BigInt with arena, z2, z1, n
    proc ecdsa_int_to_octets with z2, rolen, out_buffer
    Return 1
End Process

Note:
================================================================================
RFC 6979 deterministic k generation

Inputs:
  x  - private key (BigInt with 0 < x < n)
  h1 - hashed message bytes (hlen bytes)
  n  - curve order
  qlen, rolen - bit / byte length of n
  hash_id - SHA-2 variant

Output:
  k - BigInt with 1 <= k <= n-1
================================================================================
:End Note

Process called "ecdsa_rfc6979_generate_k" takes arena as Integer, hash_id as Integer, x as Integer, h1_bytes as Integer, hlen as Integer, n as Integer, qlen as Integer, rolen as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Implements the RFC 6979 section 3.2 algorithm. The HMAC-DRBG is
    seeded with the private key octets and bits2octets of the message
    hash; the output stream is drawn until a k in [1, n-1] is found.
    For NIST curves the bias against small k values from a single
    candidate is negligible (a fraction of 2^-(qlen-bitlen(n)) ~ 0 for
    P-256/P-384, and for P-521 the candidate q-1 is below 2^521 so the
    bias is at most 2^-256).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. V = 0x01-repeated (hlen bytes).
    2. K = 0x00-repeated (hlen bytes).
    3. K = HMAC_K(V || 0x00 || int2octets(x) || bits2octets(h1)).
    4. V = HMAC_K(V).
    5. K = HMAC_K(V || 0x01 || int2octets(x) || bits2octets(h1)).
    6. V = HMAC_K(V).
    7. Outer loop:
       T = empty
       while bitlen(T) < qlen:
           V = HMAC_K(V)
           T = T || V
       cand = bits2int(T, qlen)
       if 1 <= cand <= n-1:
           return cand
       K = HMAC_K(V || 0x00)
       V = HMAC_K(V)
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Each iteration costs (rolen+33)/hlen HMACs to refill T plus one
    HMAC to update V. Typical cost: 3-4 HMAC invocations.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Hardened against k-reuse and k-bias attacks. The HMAC-DRBG output
    is cryptographically indistinguishable from uniform given a unique
    (x, h1) pair, so k is unique per message hash.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let v_buf be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, hlen
    Let k_buf be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, hlen
    If v_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If k_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: V = 0x01-repeated, K = 0x00-repeated
    Let vi be 0
    While vi is less than hlen:
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with v_buf, vi, 1
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with k_buf, vi, 0
        Set vi to vi plus 1
    End While

    Let x_octets be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, rolen
    Let h1_octets be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, rolen
    If x_octets is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If h1_octets is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc ecdsa_int_to_octets with x, rolen, x_octets
    proc ecdsa_bits_to_octets with arena, h1_bytes, hlen, qlen, rolen, n, h1_octets

    Note: Build seed_data1 = V || 0x00 || x_oct || h1_oct
    Let seed_size be hlen plus 1 plus rolen plus rolen
    Let seed_data1 be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, seed_size
    If seed_data1 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let s_i be 0
    While s_i is less than hlen:
        Let vb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with v_buf, s_i
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with seed_data1, s_i, vb
        Set s_i to s_i plus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with seed_data1, hlen, 0
    Let xo_i be 0
    While xo_i is less than rolen:
        Let xob be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with x_octets, xo_i
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with seed_data1, hlen plus 1 plus xo_i, xob
        Set xo_i to xo_i plus 1
    End While
    Let ho_i be 0
    While ho_i is less than rolen:
        Let hob be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with h1_octets, ho_i
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with seed_data1, hlen plus 1 plus rolen plus ho_i, hob
        Set ho_i to ho_i plus 1
    End While
    Let new_k be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, hlen
    If new_k is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc ecdsa_hmac_hash with arena, hash_id, k_buf, hlen, seed_data1, seed_size, new_k
    Let k_copy_i be 0
    While k_copy_i is less than hlen:
        Let kb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with new_k, k_copy_i
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with k_buf, k_copy_i, kb
        Set k_copy_i to k_copy_i plus 1
    End While

    Note: V = HMAC_K(V)
    Let new_v be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, hlen
    If new_v is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc ecdsa_hmac_hash with arena, hash_id, k_buf, hlen, v_buf, hlen, new_v
    Let v_copy_i be 0
    While v_copy_i is less than hlen:
        Let vb2 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with new_v, v_copy_i
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with v_buf, v_copy_i, vb2
        Set v_copy_i to v_copy_i plus 1
    End While

    Note: K = HMAC_K(V || 0x01 || x_oct || h1_oct)
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with seed_data1, hlen, 1
    Let s_i2 be 0
    While s_i2 is less than hlen:
        Let vb3 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with v_buf, s_i2
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with seed_data1, s_i2, vb3
        Set s_i2 to s_i2 plus 1
    End While
    proc ecdsa_hmac_hash with arena, hash_id, k_buf, hlen, seed_data1, seed_size, new_k
    Let k_copy_j be 0
    While k_copy_j is less than hlen:
        Let kb2 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with new_k, k_copy_j
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with k_buf, k_copy_j, kb2
        Set k_copy_j to k_copy_j plus 1
    End While
    proc ecdsa_hmac_hash with arena, hash_id, k_buf, hlen, v_buf, hlen, new_v
    Let v_copy_j be 0
    While v_copy_j is less than hlen:
        Let vb4 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with new_v, v_copy_j
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with v_buf, v_copy_j, vb4
        Set v_copy_j to v_copy_j plus 1
    End While

    Note: Outer loop: build T, check candidate, retry on rejection.
    Let one_bn be proc bigint_from_u64 from BigInt with arena, 1
    Let still_searching be 1
    Let result_k be 0
    While still_searching is equal to 1:
        Note: Build T by concatenating HMAC_K(V) iterates until bitlen >= qlen.
        Let t_capacity be rolen plus hlen
        Let t_buf be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, t_capacity
        If t_buf is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let t_len be 0
        While t_len multiplied by 8 is less than qlen:
            proc ecdsa_hmac_hash with arena, hash_id, k_buf, hlen, v_buf, hlen, new_v
            Let v_copy_k be 0
            While v_copy_k is less than hlen:
                Let vb5 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with new_v, v_copy_k
                proc memory_set_byte from Memory with v_buf, v_copy_k, vb5
                proc memory_set_byte from Memory with t_buf, t_len plus v_copy_k, vb5
                Set v_copy_k to v_copy_k plus 1
            End While
            Set t_len to t_len plus hlen
        End While

        Let cand_k be proc ecdsa_bits_to_int with arena, t_buf, t_len, qlen
        If cand_k is equal to 0:
            Note: candidate is zero - reject
            Note: fall through to retry path below
        Otherwise:
            Let cmp_lo be proc bigint_compare from BigInt with cand_k, one_bn
            If cmp_lo is less than 0:
                Note: cand_k < 1 - reject
            Otherwise:
                Let cmp_hi be proc bigint_compare from BigInt with cand_k, n
                If cmp_hi is less than 0:
                    Set result_k to cand_k
                    Set still_searching to 0
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If still_searching is equal to 1:
            Note: K = HMAC_K(V || 0x00)
            Let retry_size be hlen plus 1
            Let retry_buf be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, retry_size
            If retry_buf is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Let rc_i be 0
            While rc_i is less than hlen:
                Let vb6 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with v_buf, rc_i
                proc memory_set_byte from Memory with retry_buf, rc_i, vb6
                Set rc_i to rc_i plus 1
            End While
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with retry_buf, hlen, 0
            proc ecdsa_hmac_hash with arena, hash_id, k_buf, hlen, retry_buf, retry_size, new_k
            Let k_copy_l be 0
            While k_copy_l is less than hlen:
                Let kb3 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with new_k, k_copy_l
                proc memory_set_byte from Memory with k_buf, k_copy_l, kb3
                Set k_copy_l to k_copy_l plus 1
            End While
            proc ecdsa_hmac_hash with arena, hash_id, k_buf, hlen, v_buf, hlen, new_v
            Let v_copy_m be 0
            While v_copy_m is less than hlen:
                Let vb7 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with new_v, v_copy_m
                proc memory_set_byte from Memory with v_buf, v_copy_m, vb7
                Set v_copy_m to v_copy_m plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End While
    proc secure_zero from SecureMem with k_buf, hlen
    proc secure_zero from SecureMem with v_buf, hlen
    proc secure_zero from SecureMem with x_octets, rolen
    Return result_k
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Modular inverse mod n via Fermat: x^-1 = x^(n-2) mod n
Note: Uses bigint_mod_exp with the public exponent (n - 2). Constant-time
Note: over the loop bounds; suitable for the secret-key path.
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "ecdsa_mod_inverse" takes arena as Integer, dest as Integer, x as Integer, n as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Computes dest = x^-1 mod n via Fermat's little theorem. n must be
    prime; for ECDSA n is the group order of a NIST curve, which is
    prime.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. exponent = n - 2.
    2. dest = x^exponent mod n.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Dominant cost is bigint_mod_exp over ~256/384/521 bits.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time over bit length of n (the exponent is data-dependent
    but the value n is public).
    @End Security_Scope

    Let exp_bn be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
    If exp_bn is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let two_bn be proc bigint_from_u64 from BigInt with arena, 2
    proc bigint_sub from BigInt with exp_bn, n, two_bn
    Return proc bigint_mod_exp from BigInt with arena, dest, x, exp_bn, n
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Private scalar generation: random d with 1 <= d <= n - 1
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "ecdsa_keygen_private_scalar" takes arena as Integer, n as Integer, rolen as Integer, out_d as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Generates a random private scalar uniformly in [1, n-1]. Uses
    rejection sampling on rolen-byte candidates with high-bit masking
    so the acceptance probability is at least 1/2 (RFC 6979 section 3.3
    style).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Loop:
        1. Read rolen entropic bytes.
        2. Decode as BigInt.
        3. If 1 <= candidate <= n-1, accept; else loop.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Each iteration costs an entropy draw plus a comparison. Expected
    iterations: ~1 for P-256/P-384, ~1 for P-521.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Output is the secret private key. The rejection-sampling branch
    leaks only the number of iterations (which has small variance) and
    not the value of any rejected candidate.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let one_bn be proc bigint_from_u64 from BigInt with arena, 1
    Let try_buf be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, rolen
    If try_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let attempt be 0
    Let max_attempts be 64
    While attempt is less than max_attempts:
        Let entropy_rc be proc entropy_random_bytes from Entropy with arena, try_buf, rolen
        If entropy_rc is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let cand be proc bigint_from_bytes_be from BigInt with arena, try_buf, rolen
        Let cmp_lo be proc bigint_compare from BigInt with cand, one_bn
        If cmp_lo is greater than 0 minus 1:
            Let cmp_hi be proc bigint_compare from BigInt with cand, n
            If cmp_hi is less than 0:
                Let out_cap be proc bigint_get_limb_capacity from BigInt with out_d
                Let cand_count be proc bigint_get_limb_count from BigInt with cand
                If cand_count is greater than out_cap:
                    Return 0
                End If
                Let zi be 0
                While zi is less than out_cap:
                    proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with out_d, zi, 0
                    Set zi to zi plus 1
                End While
                Let ci be 0
                While ci is less than cand_count:
                    Let lv be proc bigint_get_limb from BigInt with cand, ci
                    proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with out_d, ci, lv
                    Set ci to ci plus 1
                End While
                proc bigint_set_limb_count from BigInt with out_d, cand_count
                proc secure_zero from SecureMem with try_buf, rolen
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
        Set attempt to attempt plus 1
    End While
    proc secure_zero from SecureMem with try_buf, rolen
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ECDSA P-256: key generation, sign, verify
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "ecdsa_p256_keygen" takes arena as Integer, private_out as Integer, public_out as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Generates a P-256 keypair. The private key is a random scalar in
    [1, n-1]; the public key is private * G in Jacobian form.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Random scalar via ecdsa_keygen_private_scalar.
    2. Public point = private * G via curve_p256_scalar_mul.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Dominated by scalar multiplication (~30 ms on P-256).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Private key is secret; scalar mul is constant-time.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let n be proc curve_p256_order from P256 with arena
    Let kgen_rc be proc ecdsa_keygen_private_scalar with arena, n, 32, private_out
    If kgen_rc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let g be proc curve_p256_generator from P256 with arena
    If g is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc curve_p256_scalar_mul from P256 with arena, public_out, private_out, g
End Process

Process called "ecdsa_p256_sign" takes arena as Integer, private_key as Integer, message as Integer, message_length as Integer, sig_r_out as Integer, sig_s_out as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Signs a message with the P-256 private key using deterministic-k
    per RFC 6979. Returns (r, s) into the caller-provided BigInt
    buffers. r is computed as the x-coordinate of (k*G) mod n; s is
    (k^-1 * (h + r*d)) mod n where h is the truncated hash.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. h = SHA-256(message) reduced via bits2int to the order bit length.
    2. k = RFC 6979 deterministic-k (SHA-256-based HMAC-DRBG).
    3. R = k * G; r = R.x mod n. If r == 0, regenerate k.
    4. k_inv = k^-1 mod n.
    5. s = k_inv * (h + r * d) mod n. If s == 0, regenerate k.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Dominated by scalar mul (~30 ms) plus modular inverse (~1 ms).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time secret path: deterministic-k eliminates random
    leakage; scalar mul uses constant-time ladder; inversion uses
    Fermat over a fixed exponent.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let n be proc curve_p256_order from P256 with arena
    Let qlen be proc ecdsa_bit_length with n
    Let h1 be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 32
    If h1 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc ecdsa_hash_message with arena, ECDSA_HASH_SHA256, message, message_length, h1
    Let h_int be proc ecdsa_bits_to_int with arena, h1, 32, qlen
    If h_int is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: Reduce h_int mod n. ECDSA proceeds with h_int taken mod n in
    Note: the signing equation.
    Let h_mod be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
    If h_mod is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let h_cmp be proc bigint_compare from BigInt with h_int, n
    If h_cmp is less than 0:
        Let hc_count be proc bigint_get_limb_count from BigInt with h_int
        Let hcap be proc bigint_get_limb_capacity from BigInt with h_mod
        Let hci be 0
        While hci is less than hc_count:
            Let hlv be proc bigint_get_limb from BigInt with h_int, hci
            proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with h_mod, hci, hlv
            Set hci to hci plus 1
        End While
        proc bigint_set_limb_count from BigInt with h_mod, hc_count
    Otherwise:
        proc bigint_mod from BigInt with arena, h_mod, h_int, n
    End If

    Let g be proc curve_p256_generator from P256 with arena

    Let attempt be 0
    Let max_attempts be 16
    While attempt is less than max_attempts:
        Let k be proc ecdsa_rfc6979_generate_k with arena, ECDSA_HASH_SHA256, private_key, h1, 32, n, qlen, 32
        If k is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let kg be proc curve_p256_point_alloc from P256 with arena
        If kg is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc curve_p256_scalar_mul from P256 with arena, kg, k, g

        Note: Convert kg to affine; r = x mod n.
        Let rx_aff be proc field_p256_zero from F256 with arena
        Let ry_aff be proc field_p256_zero from F256 with arena
        Let aff_rc be proc curve_p256_to_affine from P256 with arena, kg, rx_aff, ry_aff
        If aff_rc is equal to 0:
            Set attempt to attempt plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Let r_val be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
            Let rx_cmp be proc bigint_compare from BigInt with rx_aff, n
            If rx_cmp is less than 0:
                Let rxc be proc bigint_get_limb_count from BigInt with rx_aff
                Let rxi be 0
                While rxi is less than rxc:
                    Let rxlv be proc bigint_get_limb from BigInt with rx_aff, rxi
                    proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with r_val, rxi, rxlv
                    Set rxi to rxi plus 1
                End While
                proc bigint_set_limb_count from BigInt with r_val, rxc
            Otherwise:
                proc bigint_mod from BigInt with arena, r_val, rx_aff, n
            End If
            If proc bigint_is_zero from BigInt with r_val is equal to 1:
                Set attempt to attempt plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Note: s = k^-1 * (h_mod + r*d) mod n
                Let k_inv be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
                Let inv_rc be proc ecdsa_mod_inverse with arena, k_inv, k, n
                If inv_rc is equal to 0:
                    Set attempt to attempt plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    Let rd be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
                    Let rd_prod be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
                    proc bigint_mul from BigInt with rd_prod, r_val, private_key
                    proc bigint_mod from BigInt with arena, rd, rd_prod, n

                    Let sum_hd be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
                    Let sum_temp be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
                    proc bigint_add from BigInt with sum_temp, h_mod, rd
                    Let sum_cmp be proc bigint_compare from BigInt with sum_temp, n
                    If sum_cmp is less than 0:
                        Let sc be proc bigint_get_limb_count from BigInt with sum_temp
                        Let si be 0
                        While si is less than sc:
                            Let slv be proc bigint_get_limb from BigInt with sum_temp, si
                            proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with sum_hd, si, slv
                            Set si to si plus 1
                        End While
                        proc bigint_set_limb_count from BigInt with sum_hd, sc
                    Otherwise:
                        proc bigint_mod from BigInt with arena, sum_hd, sum_temp, n
                    End If

                    Let s_prod be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
                    Let s_val be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
                    proc bigint_mul from BigInt with s_prod, k_inv, sum_hd
                    proc bigint_mod from BigInt with arena, s_val, s_prod, n

                    If proc bigint_is_zero from BigInt with s_val is equal to 1:
                        Set attempt to attempt plus 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Note: Copy r_val into sig_r_out, s_val into sig_s_out.
                        Let r_count_o be proc bigint_get_limb_count from BigInt with r_val
                        Let r_cap_o be proc bigint_get_limb_capacity from BigInt with sig_r_out
                        Let zi_r be 0
                        While zi_r is less than r_cap_o:
                            proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with sig_r_out, zi_r, 0
                            Set zi_r to zi_r plus 1
                        End While
                        Let ci_r be 0
                        While ci_r is less than r_count_o:
                            Let rlv be proc bigint_get_limb from BigInt with r_val, ci_r
                            proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with sig_r_out, ci_r, rlv
                            Set ci_r to ci_r plus 1
                        End While
                        proc bigint_set_limb_count from BigInt with sig_r_out, r_count_o

                        Let s_count_o be proc bigint_get_limb_count from BigInt with s_val
                        Let s_cap_o be proc bigint_get_limb_capacity from BigInt with sig_s_out
                        Let zi_s be 0
                        While zi_s is less than s_cap_o:
                            proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with sig_s_out, zi_s, 0
                            Set zi_s to zi_s plus 1
                        End While
                        Let ci_s be 0
                        While ci_s is less than s_count_o:
                            Let slv2 be proc bigint_get_limb from BigInt with s_val, ci_s
                            proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with sig_s_out, ci_s, slv2
                            Set ci_s to ci_s plus 1
                        End While
                        proc bigint_set_limb_count from BigInt with sig_s_out, s_count_o
                        Return 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "ecdsa_p256_verify" takes arena as Integer, public_key as Integer, message as Integer, message_length as Integer, sig_r as Integer, sig_s as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Verifies an ECDSA P-256 signature. Returns 1 if valid, 0 otherwise.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Check 0 < r < n and 0 < s < n. Reject if out of range.
    2. h = SHA-256(message) bits2int.
    3. w = s^-1 mod n.
    4. u1 = h * w mod n; u2 = r * w mod n.
    5. P = u1*G + u2*public_key.
    6. If P is infinity, reject.
    7. Accept iff (P.x mod n) == r.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Two scalar multiplications plus one inversion. ~60 ms.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Inputs are public; constant-time-ness is not required, but the
    final r comparison uses bigint_constant_time_equal.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let n be proc curve_p256_order from P256 with arena
    If proc bigint_is_zero from BigInt with sig_r is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If proc bigint_is_zero from BigInt with sig_s is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let r_cmp be proc bigint_compare from BigInt with sig_r, n
    If r_cmp is greater than 0 minus 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let s_cmp be proc bigint_compare from BigInt with sig_s, n
    If s_cmp is greater than 0 minus 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let qlen be proc ecdsa_bit_length with n
    Let h1 be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 32
    proc ecdsa_hash_message with arena, ECDSA_HASH_SHA256, message, message_length, h1
    Let h_int be proc ecdsa_bits_to_int with arena, h1, 32, qlen
    Let h_mod be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
    Let h_cmp be proc bigint_compare from BigInt with h_int, n
    If h_cmp is less than 0:
        Let hc be proc bigint_get_limb_count from BigInt with h_int
        Let hi be 0
        While hi is less than hc:
            Let hlv be proc bigint_get_limb from BigInt with h_int, hi
            proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with h_mod, hi, hlv
            Set hi to hi plus 1
        End While
        proc bigint_set_limb_count from BigInt with h_mod, hc
    Otherwise:
        proc bigint_mod from BigInt with arena, h_mod, h_int, n
    End If

    Let w be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
    Let inv_rc be proc ecdsa_mod_inverse with arena, w, sig_s, n
    If inv_rc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let u1_prod be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
    Let u1 be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
    proc bigint_mul from BigInt with u1_prod, h_mod, w
    proc bigint_mod from BigInt with arena, u1, u1_prod, n

    Let u2_prod be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
    Let u2 be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
    proc bigint_mul from BigInt with u2_prod, sig_r, w
    proc bigint_mod from BigInt with arena, u2, u2_prod, n

    Let g be proc curve_p256_generator from P256 with arena
    Let pt_a be proc curve_p256_point_alloc from P256 with arena
    Let pt_b be proc curve_p256_point_alloc from P256 with arena
    Let sum_pt be proc curve_p256_point_alloc from P256 with arena
    proc curve_p256_scalar_mul from P256 with arena, pt_a, u1, g
    proc curve_p256_scalar_mul from P256 with arena, pt_b, u2, public_key
    proc curve_p256_add from P256 with arena, sum_pt, pt_a, pt_b

    If proc curve_p256_point_is_infinity from P256 with sum_pt is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let px be proc field_p256_zero from F256 with arena
    Let py be proc field_p256_zero from F256 with arena
    Let aff_rc be proc curve_p256_to_affine from P256 with arena, sum_pt, px, py
    If aff_rc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let px_mod_n be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
    Let pxcmp be proc bigint_compare from BigInt with px, n
    If pxcmp is less than 0:
        Let pxc be proc bigint_get_limb_count from BigInt with px
        Let pxi be 0
        While pxi is less than pxc:
            Let plv be proc bigint_get_limb from BigInt with px, pxi
            proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with px_mod_n, pxi, plv
            Set pxi to pxi plus 1
        End While
        proc bigint_set_limb_count from BigInt with px_mod_n, pxc
    Otherwise:
        proc bigint_mod from BigInt with arena, px_mod_n, px, n
    End If

    Return proc bigint_constant_time_equal from BigIntX with px_mod_n, sig_r
End Process

